parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to stiffen or lock, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

the vehicle is difficult to steer

especially during turns
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to get stuck in the ignition, preventing the engine from turning off, and leaving the lights and radio on. This can lead to safety issues, such as the risk of theft or accident.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition switch
will not turn all the way to off
radio and lights stay on
and the key cannot be removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, such as headlights, brake lights, and infotainment systems, which can lead to safety issues, such as reduced visibility or loss of control.

driver side running light keeps failing to illuminate
driver side rear brake lights keep failing
rear passenger side reverse light and blinker failing to illuminate
audio echo
volume control issues
and display blackouts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Engine dies
loss of brakes

smoke in the console area

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to uncertainty about the fuel level, which can cause safety issues, such as running out of fuel while driving.
